<TITLE> Mamun gets bail in extortion case </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 27 (bdnews24.com)The Supreme Court has granted bail to controversial businessman Giasuddin Al-Mamun in an extortion case. The three-member Appellate Division bench headed by Md Fazlul Karim made the order on Thursday. The bail will be effective until the submission of investigation report by police. Barrister Rafique-ul-Haque presented Mamun's case in the hearing. Businessman Harun Ferdous filed the case with Gulshan Police Station on Mar 27, 2007. The High Court allowed him bail on July 1 that year. The Appellate Division stayed the bail order on July 6 the same year. bdne
